The article discusses a national security memorandum outlining the revitalization of national security and foreign policy institutions in the United States. The memorandum emphasizes the importance of integrity, transparency, diversity, modernization, service, and accountability within these institutions. It also highlights the need to strengthen the national security workforce, improve partnerships and engagement with various actors, and implement a foreign policy that benefits the American middle class. The memorandum establishes an Interagency Working Group on the National Security Workforce to coordinate efforts and sets deadlines for reports and assessments on progress.